<document>
	<title>ALPHA-Amylase activity in sweat and serum of patients with cystic
   fibrosis of the pancreas.</title>

	<author>Nikolaejek-W-P.</author>
	<author>Emrich-H-M.</author>

	<source>Eur-J-Pediatr. 1976 Jul 12. 122(4). P 289-91.</source>

	<abstract>The hypothesis by Doggett and Harrison, according to which alpha-
   amylase is the pathogenic factor of the exocrinopathy in cystic
   fibrosis (C.F.), is investigated.No elevation of alpha-amylase in
   sweat and serum of C.F. patients, as compared with controls of
   similar age, is observed. It is concluded that the &quot;C.F. factor&quot;
   cannot be identified with alpha-amylase.</abstract>

